      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Grahame Begg's NZ recruit THIS TIME GIRL (3) finished out of the money when fresh two starts back then was beaten 5.5 lengths when fourth in a 1600m contest at Sandown-Hillside, Faces an easier assignment here and should be nearing peak fitness, so looks the testing material. DIDN'T MISS MANY (2) finished fourth first-up from a spell last start over 1412m at Geelong after racing on the pace for much of the way. Hasn't finished further back than second in three second-up runs and strikes the right race to maintain that record here. ON BROADWAY (7) will take benefit from this run but rarely misses a trifecta spot and has been trialling well. VILLA SEVENTYNINE (4) will be better for the two runs back after coming from the NT but rises in grade here.",
